Adult male.description: Baltimore Orioles are larger than American Redstarts with a longer bill. Adult males have an entirely orange belly unlike adult male American Redstarts, which have orange on the sides of the upper breast.

Adult female.description: Baltimore Orioles are larger than American Redstarts with a longer bill. Adult female Baltimore Orioles have yellowish orange underparts unlike male or female American Redstarts, which have mostly white underparts.

Female/immature.description: Females/immatures Magnolia Warblers have a yellow belly unlike American Redstarts.
